title: Grateful Dead Live at The Spectrum on 1993-09-14
lineage: Schoeps mk41's/CMC3 > Tascam DA-P1 > CDR > EAC (secure) > CD Wave > Cool Edit Pro > mkwACT > SHN (seekable)
description: Help On The Way-> Slipknot!-> Franklin's Tower, Minglewood Blues, Broken Arrow, Brown Eyed Women, When I Paint My Masterpiece, Bird Song Iko Iko, Looks Like Rain, Way To Go Home, Crazy Fingers, Corinna-> Drums-> Jam-> The Last Time-> Wharf Rat-> Sugar Magnolia, E: Brokedown Palace

reviews.review_text:
Hidden gem Hadn't heard this show since the night it happened, and a lot of muddy water under the bridge since then. 

Wow, what a night. First off, when was the last time a bad show started off with Help/Slip/Franklin's? But what makes this special is that from the first notes the band is obviously having as much fun as the audience, not always the case with 90's shows. The up vibe certainly lifted Jerry's playing, and a joy pervades the entire show. Download it for that, if nothing else, and if you can keep yourself from dancing, well, then, get off the bus.

Only minor downer is the recording. Super clear aud, and it captures the crowd vibe(check out the solo in Iko)perfectly, but for some reason the balance is biased right. Jerry centric, but what the hey...

Almost The show was ok. Ever notice they'd often do Help>Slip>Franks the night after Dark Star as a consolation prize? The first set was tight then the Iko was intense but Jerry sort of lost it for a while ..
There was this dude outside who looked just like Jerry- not that long island dude who was always at shows this was a different dude. At first he was smiling then I think he was like, ok I'm not him quit staring..
Last Time was fun I never thought it meant anything really

Last of the great Ones I'd have to say this was the last really great SHOW I saw them do. I saw some good sets and great versions after this but this SHOW was right on the money from the opening chords of Help on the way to when they absolutely brought the ceiling down at end of Wharf Rat and had a nice extended Sugar Magnolia. Jerry definitely had comfortble shoes on that night. This is the show that convinced me I can enjoy this band as a Wharf Rat.

Very Nice I'm not a big fan of "Minglewood" but there's a few that really get me going..this one is near the top of the list.

Very nice show..one of the few post 92(last time I saw 'em) shows I want to have.

Jim

Fare you well This unfortunately was my last show I saw them perform and what a show it was. The entire '93 summer tour was awesome. I had so much fun and the music was incredible. So my last song I ever saw them play was Brokedown Palace. I was on Jerry's side of the stage and watched him walk off behind the stage into the tunnel, put a jacket on, light a cigarette and disappeared into eternity. I didn't know then that it would be the last time I saw him but I remember singing in my head..."Fare you well" as he disappeared in the tunnel. Thank you JG for the inspiration, the memories & most of all the music.
the Spectrum rocked This 3 show run at the Spectrum was great and there pretty much were no rules inside or outside of the arena.  Miss the good old days.
